<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-06-13T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-06-13T15:00:00-05:00" n="740" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d740">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18399</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Special Representative <persName type="to">Rodgers</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-06-13T15:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 13, 1916, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>135. Leader of recent raid above Laredo, wearing Carranza uniform and
                            insignia, has been killed. Papers on body showed him to be Lieutenant
                            Colonel Villareal of Carranza Army. Body was also identified by one of
                            the prisoners taken.</p>
                        <p>Immediately inform appropriate authorities.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>